\begin_layout Standard
This section assumes you have done a standard install from the Live CD.
 After installation it is recommended that you connect the computer to the
 Internet and wait for the update manager to pop up and get the latest updates
 for EMC and Ubuntu before continuing.
 For more complex installations see the Integrators Manual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Latency Test
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Latency Test determines how late your computer processor is in responding
 to a request.
 Some hardware can interrupt the processing which could cause missed steps
 when running a CNC machine.
 This is the first thing you need to do.
 Follow the instructions in section (
\begin_inset LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Latency-Test"

\end_inset

) to run the latency test.
\end_layout

